===Etymology===
Old English ''[[non#Old English|nōn]]'', from a Germanic borrowing of classical Latin ''[[nona|nōna]]'' ‘ninth hour’ (short for ''[[nona|nōna]] [[hora#Latin|hōra]]''), feminine of ''[[nonus|nōnus]]'' ‘ninth’.  Cognate with Flemish ''[[noen]]'', obsolete German ''[[Non]]'', Norwegian ''[[non#Norwegian|non]]''.

